The elevator did not reach the highest level, the most irritating is the sound insulation effect is very poor, the door noise of other rooms, the phone call noise, the elevator lifting noise, etc., almost did not let you sleep. The garbage in the hotel room needs to be taken to the outside trash can. Isn't room service what a hotel is all about?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tamara C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We spent one night at Grand Garden Hotel Yangon as a layover between a flight from Inle Lake and one to Jaipur via Bangkok. As others have said, this hotel is very close (5 minutes) from the Yangon airport and very convenient for an overnight stay pre-flight. The pick up and drop off were prompt and all we could hope for. I booked a standard room, and we were first put in a 3rd floor (top floor) room. This room would have been unbearable. These top rooms sit under a slanted roof that appeared to be uninsulated since we could see light shining through in places. This meant that the ceiling of the room (the roof) was one large radiant heater. The finish-out in the room and bathroom was less than expected as well. When I called downstairs to say the heat was unbearable, they quickly moved us to an upgraded 2nd floor room that was perfectly cool and much more nicely finished out, so all was good. Food was good if not remarkable. The pool was dingy looking, so we passed on that. There is a fitness center in a building across the parking lot, but it was very warm inside. We walked the street outside the compound: Some interesting bits, but definitely a suburban slum and no sidewalks. My 4-star rating would probably be a 3.5, but the location and free shuttle service are excellent for airport access and the upgraded room was very nice. So, if like us, all you need is a clean, convenient and well-priced overnight stay near the airport, Grand Garden Hotel Yangon is the ticket. Staff is friendly and helpful as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joao Carlos V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Besides having communicated the hotel our arriving time, flights, etc... They never sent someone to pick us up.|No apologies were offered.|The hotel is nice, clean, confortable beds, large rooms, tv, minibar, porter service, lift...|We were given the wrong bed configuration at first, then we were moved, but it ended up being a smaller room. Since we were only there for the night, we didn't bother in complaining.|At 3am we needed to leave to the airport, and it was very hard to wake the receptionist up. He called us the transfer and went straight back to sleep.|","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andy Moughtin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKJcsUB6yttRBkpYAduYRKBMRN887AyNcIXhbtwXEJ1Fg0sH3IW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Only spent a night here. Hotel seemed great. Room very comfy with lots of thoughtful touches. Staff very friendly and helpful. One down side was that the lift doesn't go to the third floor (could be an issue for some) and the rain was so noisy on the roof. Floors 1 and 2 wouldn't have this I'm sure.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emilia Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJGB2yQDyIcbSK2hsJbAE9abhwtxurcMu9ReWa82CZwgxxYstk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I stayed in this hotel for two days. The room I had was very clean especially the bathroom. Location of the hotel is near the airport and if you want to go to the city just called the taxi to the airport and then you go by bus cause the price high by taxi.The breakfast in the hotel is average but your stomage will full. Unfortunately while there is swimming pool in this hotel but we can't swim because of the renovation of the pool.,didn't know until when. Cause Yangon is very hot and dusty this hotel is like hidden gem. And as I lover cat 🐈 I was surprised that in this hotel I saw the cute cat in front of the hotel! What a lovely hotel!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Seung-won Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXU2hasb5KMwlpVJIEoMIaSSwPIwVA8cdf1uPPQ5GdoFw8-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It is a good transit hotel near Yangon International Airport with moderate room rate, if you do not expect a cozy place for relaxation with tranquility and long stay.

The hotel suggests free airport pickup and sending that would take less than 8 minutes. For airport pickup, call the reception and wait 10 minutes at designated place. In a while you can find a hotel staff strolling around holding a sheet of paper printed hotel name on.

They will suggest you a breakfast box if you have to leave too early to have hotel breakfast: simple sandwich, a boiled egg, and a bottle of water.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jo B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is very reasonable for the price. The staff are very helpful and very friendly especially if you’re travelling on your own as I was. The room was clean and looked nice. It was a little noisy by the road and and the blinds didn’t really keep the light out. Apart from those minor issues it was a good stay and very good service","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kian wee chau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVc4qC3YFjs7c-ek9IZoWDoPgw4w6OoEt6GFySRD1pmiW4DyifM9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I stayed in this hotel one night.
Pro:
1) The room is very bright.
2) Pillow has different softness.
3) The room is new.
4) The receptionists are friendly.
5) It provides free airport drop off / pickup.
6) It provides massage services. MMK 8,000 per hour. Hotel guest has 25% discount which is MMK 6,000.
7) WiFi signal is good and fast.
8) Dinner at restaurant was delicious for what I ordered. There were Steamed fish, Tom yum soup and black pepper prawn.
Con:
1) The swimming pool area is lack of regular cleaning. The concrete floor next to the pool has obvious dirty stain.
2) The window curtains can't block the day light. When sun rises, I can feel the day light already. My sleep was disturbed. 2 pictures were taken without turning on any light in the room.
3) The balcony door doesn't have any curtains at all. This is another source of day light that disturbing my sleep.
4) Many mosquito were in the restaurant.
5) Buffet breakfast offered simple choices. Local food, bread, porridge, typical Indian food, fruits.
6) Varieties of TV programs are limited. Only few are English. Signal was not good too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPamBSjoI0PwMKEXt4W9c2yruVdrGkUGIYdg6f7&fid=0x0:0x43a270e8c9d016f8"],"When":"2019-10-4"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Doreen W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel suits our needs very well. The cleanliness, good shower, good wifi, superb breakfast (including a box lunch for early departures), location, and other amenities are present. What sets in a high rating for us is the sincere dedication of the staff.  On one of our stays, they arranged our transport away from Yangon and, on our return late in the evening a week later, a different shift handed us our transportation arrangements for the following morning, including bus tickets and an arranged taxi at a fixed price. By the time we leave Myanmar this trip, we will have stayed at High Five 4 times and will look forward to future visits.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mary M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I needed a one night hotel near the airport as I was coming in at midnight and leaving to Inle Lake at 8am. They asked all the right questions: do you need a wake up call, a packed breakfast for the early flight, a taxi. They offered advice about payments, time I would need in the airport.  WiFi was great. Electric kettle in working order. Plenty of sockets for charging. Table for working or eating. Reaaonsble mini bar. Good location should one want a mini market.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Martin S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Room was clean and secure. Hot water/shower available you just need to remember to turn the water heater on 10-15 mins before you need it. ||Smell of smoking in the room (despite no smoking signs everywhere) but cleared when we opened the window. ||Beware that there are no lifts to the upper floors but staff are more than willing (and able) to carry your luggage to/from your room.||Ate in the restaurant (next to reception) and food acceptable and reasonably priced.||Hotel organised early morning taxi to airport (5000kyat) and packed us a take away breakfast (water, sandwich, hard boiled egg, cake) which we ate at the airport as we left before breakfast time.||Staff very good and happy to recommend if you are looking for a convenient hotel near to the airport.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pyae Phyo Kyaw","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFylRrAk2RJmyh_T2cHUW4zpnPnI8IcKHXYQPi475qtna6H4Ob_A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Not a particularly cozy place, but only 15 minute drive from Yangon International airport as well as a decent enough place for an overnight stay. owner: {"id":"","name":"丹瑞卡亚尔斯恩酒店 Hotel Shwe Kyal SIN (Owner)","link":""}
user_reviews: [{"Name":"LuckyTraveller17","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We were booked into this hotel by Burmese friends as it was close to their home  -  an important factor as we were taken to their home for our mid-day and evening meals.
